        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          How much should I invest in Google Ads to see results?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          For local businesses on the Treasure Coast, a starting budget of $400–$800 per month allows competitive campaigns in most service categories. Cost per click varies by industry — legal, medical, and home improvement services tend to be higher than restaurants or salons. We give you a realistic estimate before you commit to anything.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          What is the difference between Google Ads and organic SEO?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          Google Ads places you at the top of results immediately — you pay per click. Organic SEO earns free placement over time but takes months to build. For local businesses that need customers now, Ads is faster. SEO builds long-term visibility. The ideal strategy combines both: Ads for immediate results while SEO matures in the background.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          Google Ads or Meta Ads — which should I invest in first?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          Google Ads captures customers who are already actively searching for your service — more efficient when there is clear demand ("plumber Port St. Lucie," "dentist Fort Pierce"). <a href="/en/services/facebook-instagram-ads-treasure-coast/" class="font-medium hover:underline" style="color:var(--primary)">Meta Ads</a> is better for building awareness or promoting offers to audiences who do not know you yet. For high-intent service searches, Google Ads is usually the more profitable first investment.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
